Documents reporter in docx, odt, pdf, xhtml and pptx formats using Java POJO.
Supported templates formats: docx and odt

Using technologies: Maven, Spring Framework, DocxReporter, Apache Velocity, Freemarker. Testing: JUnit, Mockito

Example:
We have model tree (see in https://github.com/creepid/DocsReporter/tree/master/src/test/java/by/creepid/docsreporter/model):

public class Project {

    private String name;
    private Date date;
    private BigDecimal price;
    private String author = null;
    private int stuffSize;
    private Manager manager;
    private List<DeveloperWithPhoto> developers;
    private byte[] logo;

    //constructors, getters and setters
}

where:

public class Developer {

    private String name;
    private String lastName;
    private String mail;
    private Date birthDate;
    private List<Role> roles;
    private WorkingStatus status = WorkingStatus.fullTime;
    
    //constructors, getters and setters

}

public class DeveloperWithPhoto extends Developer {

    private byte[] photo;
    
    //constructors, getters and setters

}

And template in .docx (https://github.com/creepid/DocsReporter/blob/master/src/test/resources/DocxProjectWithVelocity.docx for example):



